    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                Visucio <lb n="2"/>aedem cum signo <lb n="3"/><expan><abbr>C</abbr><ex>aius</ex></expan> Candidius <lb n="4"/>Calpurnianus <lb n="5"/><expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>ecurio</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>c</abbr><ex>ivium</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>c</abbr><ex>ivitatis</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>S</abbr><ex>ueborum</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>N</abbr><ex>icrensium</ex></expan> item <expan><abbr>dec</abbr><ex>urio</ex></expan> <supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>c</abbr><ex>ivium</ex></expan></supplied> <lb n="6"/><expan><abbr>c</abbr><ex>ivitatis</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Nemet</abbr><ex>um</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>fec</abbr><ex>it</ex></expan>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Allseitig abgearbeitetes Fragment einer Tafel. Z. 2: ED-, EM-Ligaturen; Z. 3: ND-Ligatur; Z. 4: AL-, AN-Ligaturen; Z. 5: ITE-, MDE-Ligaturen; D und C ineinander verschränkt; Z. 6: NE-, ME-Ligaturen. Der Stifter war decurio zweier verschiedener, angrenzender civitates.</p>
            </div>
